    "paragraph": {
      "rich_text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": {
            "content": "We arrive at Nhambavale Lodge, which was picked on the map at random - as just a convenient place to stop to break up our drive - we weren’t expecting much from it. While telling the receptionist how much I hate crocodiles, we spot the house we’re staying in. Although it resembles a Weavers nest more than a house. An organic mound of grass with a front door, we’ve arrived at Casa Grande (they gave us the “big house” as the whole place was empty). ",
            "link": null
          },
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          },
          "plain_text": "We arrive at Nhambavale Lodge, which was picked on the map at random - as just a convenient place to stop to break up our drive - we weren’t expecting much from it. While telling the receptionist how much I hate crocodiles, we spot the house we’re staying in. Although it resembles a Weavers nest more than a house. An organic mound of grass with a front door, we’ve arrived at Casa Grande (they gave us the “big house” as the whole place was empty). ",
